A note... The pixmap specs allow the first line to have 6 instead of 4 parameters; the last two can contain the x and y hotspot position for the case the pixmap is used as a cursor.
Would it be *hard* to make the x and y parameter in the cursor_new_from_pixmap optional (default 0,0) and try to use the hotspot coordinates from the first line of the pixmap array?
