Hi!

Sometimes I've asked me, whats the difference between the 
php_gtk.exe and the php_win.exe.

So, the difference is only that the php_gtk.exe is also 
aviable to make associations to the file name extension 
*.php-gtk. Or is there any other feature I don't know 
about?

For the php_win.exe I asked myself why there is so much 
source code when somethin like the following should work 
also..

>#include <stdio.h>
>#include <stdlib.h>
>#include <windows.h>
>
>#define EXE_FILENAME "phpgtk.exe"
>
>void basedir(char *path, char *buffer, int buffer_size)
>{
>  char res[buffer_size], cache[buffer_size]; 
>  int pos=0, len=0;
>  //Length of path..
>  len = strlen(path)-strlen(EXE_FILENAME);
>  //Put firs character to res..
>  sprintf(res, "%c%", path[0]);
>  //Cache chars to lenght of path..
>  for(pos=1;pos<len;pos++)
>  {
>    sprintf(res, "%s%c", res, path[pos]);
>  }
>  //return result..
>  strcpy(buffer, res); 
>}
>     
>int main(int argc, char *argv[])
>{
>  char dir[500], php_file[500], php_path[500];
>  //The paths..
>  basedir(argv[0], php_path, 500);
>  sprintf(php_path, "\"%s\\php.exe\"", php_path);
>  strcpy(php_file, argv[1]);
>  //Run it..
>  ShellExecute(NULL, NULL, php_path, php_file, NULL, SW_HIDE);
>  return 0;
>}
(not tested yet)

So, please help me: Why and When it's better to use one of 
those (php_gtk/php_win.exe)? I don't understand :-/

Sorry if my question is absurd, but was confused about 
this..

Regards, Florian
